    {
      "key": "e4f209c6-40cb-4ef9-97c6-fb7fffc7b5bf",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e4f209c6-40cb-4ef9-97c6-fb7fffc7b5bf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "324e20b1-7938-40b4-a366-dbc18746e70f",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to introduce the steps students will take on Day 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Display the Before and After Artifact examples. As you walk through each one:\n- Point out how the Before artifact shows the issue in context — what’s happening, what’s going wrong, and how it affects the user\n- Highlight whether the artifact includes important messages, actions, or design flaws that help explain the problem\n- Then, show the After artifact, and explain how it shows what was redesigned, what changed, and how it improves the experience\n- Emphasize the personified security solutions and what they communicate — what the features do and why they help users\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Display the Before Artifact example. As you walk through it:\n- Point out how the Before artifact shows the issue in context — what's happening, what's going wrong, and how it affects the user.\n- Highlight whether the artifact includes important messages, actions, or design flaws that help explain the problem.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Display the After Artifact example. As you walk through it:\n- Explain how it shows what was redesigned, what changed, and how it improves the experience\n- Emphasize the personified security solutions and what they communicate — what the features do and why they help users"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "324e20b1-7938-40b4-a366-dbc18746e70f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b25f654-e9d8-4ebe-aeb5-5d47cc48cf12",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa-solid fa-bullseye-arrow\"></i> **Goal of this activity:** Have students analyze an app through a user-centered design process that begins with them evaluating empathy maps.",
        "duration": "25",
        "name": "Investigate the System"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b25f654-e9d8-4ebe-aeb5-5d47cc48cf12",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5ad564ab-0af7-4fc9-af19-9025b38c89c5",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now that you understand the structure of the project, let’s begin the first step: analyzing a real-world system from two user perspectives. Today you’ll choose an app, explore what different users need, and identify at least two problems in the system. You’ll decide whether those problems are related to security, usability, or both — and then create a Before artifact that shows what’s going wrong.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5ad564ab-0af7-4fc9-af19-9025b38c89c5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "758b6561-1b4e-4166-80e8-3ecea45c8cf7",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 2, Level 1 to complete Level 1 to choose an app. Remind them to follow the steps in the Day 1 section investigating their chosen system, analyzing user needs using the empathy maps, and identifying two distinct issues to focus on.",
        "progression_name": "Choose an App"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "758b6561-1b4e-4166-80e8-3ecea45c8cf7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "68646cd4-9f6c-4ea9-aa26-ef5042925fde",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students work, check in to ensure they’re grounding their issues in the user needs from the empathy maps. Encourage them to explain why the problems they’ve identified matter to the user, and offer support to students who seem stuck by helping them revisit the user's perspective."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "68646cd4-9f6c-4ea9-aa26-ef5042925fde",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1061a869-f9ff-430a-a704-f6522716ca0f",
      "position": 15,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to answer the reflection question in Day 1 Reflection in their Project Planning Guide.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use these responses to identify common misconceptions or highlight strong thinking you can share at the start of Day 2."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1061a869-f9ff-430a-a704-f6522716ca0f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "774a9238-9c46-4594-b1b4-89d1a8847e1e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "41eea447-d2b1-4361-9409-3a4f89aef684",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you think makes a security feature feel helpful vs. frustrating?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should begin thinking about the tension between protecting users and keeping systems easy to use. This warm-up helps them reflect on their own experiences with security features and prepares them to design solutions that balance security and usability in today’s activity.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "41eea447-d2b1-4361-9409-3a4f89aef684",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4644f5b0-ec8d-43da-92fb-123b26536117",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Day 2 tasks with students. Explain that today they'll design solutions for the two issues they identified last class by choosing defense mechanisms, explaining how their fixes work, and creating an After artifact that shows the improved system.",
        "duration": "35",
        "name": "Designing Solutions"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4644f5b0-ec8d-43da-92fb-123b26536117",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b8f5e93f-2352-43bc-bac8-a2f040e07800",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You're now working through the Day 2 section of your Project Guide. Take your time choosing a meaningful solution for each issue, and think carefully about how your design affects both security and usability.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b8f5e93f-2352-43bc-bac8-a2f040e07800",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f25a5bde-12fe-421f-b0fc-e68861bae6d4",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Let students manage their own progress while following the steps in the guide. Encourage them to move at their own pace but to complete all four parts: choosing solutions, explaining tradeoffs, creating their After artifacts, and getting peer feedback.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students work, check in on whether they're connecting their solutions back to the user’s original needs. Ask how their fixes will help real users and what makes their design easy or hard to use. Offer reminders about using Level 2 for solution brainstorming or Level 3 for personifying their defense mechanism.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Check that students are applying their feedback and not just moving on without revising. Ask how their redesigned system helps users and what their personified security solution is doing to protect them. Encourage creativity while keeping focus on clarity and purpose.",
        "progression_name": "Explore Issues and Defenses"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f25a5bde-12fe-421f-b0fc-e68861bae6d4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5e07b16d-c756-488c-8d2f-8766d5673b2d",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** About halfway through the work time, pause the class to make sure everyone gets a chance to hear how their work is landing. Even if students aren’t completely done with their solutions or artifacts, they can still get useful feedback on what they’ve done so far. Instruct them to trade project guides and artifacts with another group and use the Peer Feedback questions in their guide to give thoughtful responses. If needed, model how to respond by reading one question aloud and offering an example answer.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students give feedback, listen for thoughtful responses and help students explain their reasoning. Encourage them to ask clarifying questions or suggest improvements, not just compliments.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to make any revisions based on their peer feedback and continue working on their two After artifacts. Remind them that their artifact should clearly show what changed and include a personified security feature. Students can use Level 3 to help with brainstorming artifact ideas or writing what their security mechanism might say or do.",
        "progression_name": "Planning Your Creative Artifact"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5e07b16d-c756-488c-8d2f-8766d5673b2d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9e60dea1-c63c-4a6d-a6d1-4016ddeab1ed",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to answer the Day 2 Reflection questions in their Project Planning Guide. Let them know this is their chance to reflect on the design choices they made today and how they balanced security and usability in their solutions.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Optionally, you can have students record their answers to these questions on a 3x5 card or scrap piece of paper to be handed in as an Exit Ticket as they leave the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9e60dea1-c63c-4a6d-a6d1-4016ddeab1ed",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f9c1f343-974c-40f5-bcd0-9d3fae5cfe45"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ff7a1073-94f0-4e16-b100-a9b42ae6d165",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What is a trade-off that you had to make to keep your system secure but still easy to use?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should be able to explain how they are balancing security and usability in their own apps. They should be able to reference specific CIA pillars or AAA frameworks they are employing to maintain high levels of security. They should be able to lean on principles of user-centered design to explain how they are maintaining usability for all app users.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ff7a1073-94f0-4e16-b100-a9b42ae6d165",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f8d73458-a010-49b7-9744-83b0012a4192",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Day 3 tasks. Let them know today is about wrapping up and sharing their work. They'll finish any edits to their After artifacts, participate in a Gallery Walk to see each other's ideas, and complete a short reflection about what they learned from the project and their design choices.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Give students about 15 minutes to make any final updates to their After artifacts before sharing. Encourage them to use the peer feedback they received, reflect on teacher check-ins, or make improvements based on their own ideas. Remind them to double-check that their personified security feature is clear and that the artifact communicates what changed in the system.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Finalize Your Work"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f8d73458-a010-49b7-9744-83b0012a4192",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cdc04120-6d60-4edf-80ad-3d2c124652d0",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students set up their Before and After artifacts around the room. Explain that they'll be participating in a Gallery Walk, viewing and responding to each other's work using sticky notes or comment cards.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Gallery Walk Share-Out",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If space or class size is limited, consider rotating groups through “stations” or assigning starting points so traffic flows more evenly."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cdc04120-6d60-4edf-80ad-3d2c124652d0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "669942ba-984d-4b52-8e1d-5f0d925f4201",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students reflect on the decisions they made in their redesigns, especially how they balanced security and usability. Direct them to complete the End of Project Reflection in their Project Planning Guide. This is a chance for students to think critically about their final choices and what they learned from the process.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time allows, invite a few students to share one insight from their reflection with the class to wrap up the unit on a thoughtful note."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "669942ba-984d-4b52-8e1d-5f0d925f4201",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "de635123-dcac-438c-b402-6a9c59fcda52",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "de635123-dcac-438c-b402-6a9c59fcda52",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d0591dff-d378-43bc-bac6-72ff0389f7cc",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 13, Level 4 to complete the End of Lesson Survey."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d0591dff-d378-43bc-bac6-72ff0389f7cc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c4e23dea-5f0e-4453-afbe-4e595d3b0642"
